OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FEnergy bills to rise and   
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Ffall quicker in shake-up   
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Household energy bills will change     
OL,6, every three months under new plans     
OL,7, aimed at avoiding price shocks.        
OL,9,FCurrently, the price cap - the maximum 
OL,10,Famount suppliers can charge their      
OL,11,Fcustomers in England, Scotland and     
OL,12,FWales - changes every six months.      
OL,14,FEnergy regulator Ofgem says the change 
OL,15,Fmeans price rises and falls will be    
OL,16,Fpassed on to customers more quickly.   
OL,18,FEnergy bills soared in April and are   
OL,19,Fexpected to rise sharply again in      
OL,20,FOctober, when the cap goes up.         
